review_title: Fits perfectly with my Sennheiser HD 4.40 headphones
reviews: This is a simple and straight-forward case that will keep your headphones safe from scratches and falls, at half the price of other cases on the market. I definitely recommend these if you're looking for a rugged case for your foldable headphones.

review_title: A doll so life-like you'd think it was a real girl
reviews: I bought this as a gift for my niece and she loves it! She loves the way the doll is able to move around and walk on its own. Sometimes, while driving home from my sister's house, I see the doll in the rear-view mirror and have to constantly remind my niece to stop leaving her things in my car. She brings it everywhere so she must love this doll. This doll, however, must love me because I woke up the other day and saw the doll peeking at me through my bedroom window. Of all the places to leave her toys..... Kids will be kids, I guess. Although, if given the option, I would have docked a .5 out of my rating because my sister has been complaining that the doll cries in the middle of the night.
This is a nice, sturdy-looking high-profile cap.

Product arrived exactly how it looked in the pictures. This is probably one of my new favorite go-to caps for its quality and fit. It's got a stiff crown and is high-profile, so if you have a small head I can see these hats being a tad too big for you. I have a big head so this hat is perfect for me.
It's a nice laid-back snapback that isn't too imposing. There's a mesh sleeve behind the crown which is a nice touch, as the crown would be extremely floppy without it.
I've ordered a couple of these caps and the sizes were inconsistent. The grey, burgundy and blue caps fit me perfectly, while the khaki and black caps seemed more shallow.

review_title: You get what you pay for
reviews: The blade is beginning to rust in its holster.

review_title: Very sturdy sleeve for your tablet
reviews: I love to put my tablet, and even some books, into this sleeve to protect them from all the other stuff moving around in my backpack.

review_title: Sound is very muffled and lacks bass/clarity
reviews: These earphones are extremely stylish and have a good look going for it, but the sound quality leaves a lot to be desired.

review_title: The perfect swan song for Mr. Hayao Miyazaki
reviews: I watch this movie at least twice and year, and each time it turns me into a blubbery mess. I love everything about it, from it's excellent soundtrack (by industry vet, Joe Hisaishi) to it's likeable cast of characters. This is a definite must-watch.

review_title: Best water bottle I've ever used
reviews: This is an excellent water bottle to take to school/work, due to its size and sturdy construction. This will not give your water a weird taste like most other water bottles and it's very easy to clean.

review_title: People weren't kidding about the battery life... it's incredible.
reviews: I've owned this controller for half a year and it's only gone down two bars.

review_title: Great game, reminds me of Silent Hill
reviews: I enjoyed this game a lot more than it's prequel. it's very eerie and the locations the game has you traverse were very detailed and well-made.

review_title: An excellent pair of running tights at half the price of major brands
reviews: I love running in these more than my Asics thermal tights. They fit very snug, while still providing me with a full range of motion. They *are* a bit long on me, but I don't have the longest legs so don't let my issue deter you from an otherwise great product.
Great looking patch and very authentic to its source material.

review_title: A must-have for Amy Winehouse fans or jazz fans in general
reviews: This is an amazing collection of Amy's Live in London concert and her Porchester Hall session. It contains live peformances of most of her popular songs off her Frank and Back To Black albums including Rehab, Valerie, Just Friends, and Some Unholy War (my personal favorite). The quality is so crisp and detailed that it feels like you're there watching her perform live.

review_title: A great hat to keep you warm through the harshest of winters
reviews: I'm in love with this beanie. It knows how to take a "-30C Canadian winter" beating.

review_title: Make sure to buy one size larger!
reviews: First of all I'd like to say that this is an excellent value for such a high quality fitted cap. I'm docking one star from a perfect score because the sizing is a bit misleading. Most of my fitted caps are in the M/L sizes and after reading how this hat runs a size smaller than average, I opted for the L/XL. To my surprise, the cap was still quite tight on my head. Luckily my dad's birthday is coming up so I'll be gifting this one to him and ordering an XL/XXL cap for myself.
Screen protector went on effortlessly, without any bubbles. 10/10 would buy again.
